===========================================================================

Use firefox instead.  (And install that using Debian.)

===========================================================================

Mozilla 1.7:

cd ~/tmp
wget http://ftp.mozilla.org/pub/mozilla.org/mozilla/releases/mozilla1.7/mozilla-i686-pc-linux-gnu-1.7-installer.tar.gz
tar zxf mozilla-i686-pc-linux-gnu-1.7-installer.tar.gz
cd mozilla-installer
sudo ./mozilla-installer
# laptop: install into /usr/local/mozilla1.7 (default is /usr/local/mozilla)
# pag: install into /usr/local/pkg/mozilla/mozilla-1.7
# Don't let mozilla run at the end of the mozilla-installer script, lest
# files in ~/.mozilla be owned by root.

## Personal setup: 2 versions
## Version 1 (for pag)
cd /usr/local/bin
sudo cp mozilla16 mozilla17
sudo rm -f mozilla
sudo ln -s mozilla17 mozilla
# rm -f ~/bin/Linux-i686/mozilla
# ln -fs /usr/local/mozilla-1.7/mozilla ~/bin/Linux-i686
# (cd ~/bin/Linux-i686; ln -s mozilla netscape)
## Version 2 (for laptop)
cd /usr/local/bin; sudo rm -f mozilla; sudo ln -s /usr/local/mozilla1.7/mozilla .

Customizations: see file "~/wisdom/pc-setup" (see Mozilla section)

===========================================================================

Mozilla 1.6:

cd ~/tmp
wget http://ftp.mozilla.org/pub/mozilla.org/mozilla/releases/mozilla1.6/mozilla-i686-pc-linux-gnu-1.6-installer.tar.gz
tar zxf mozilla-i686-pc-linux-gnu-1.6-installer.tar.gz
cd mozilla-installer
sudo ./mozilla-installer
# laptop: install into /usr/local/mozilla1.6 (default is /usr/local/mozilla)
# pag: install into /usr/local/pkg/mozilla/mozilla-1.6
# Don't let mozilla run at the end of the mozilla-installer script, lest
# files in ~/.mozilla be owned by root.
# Personal setup: 2 versions
# Version 1 (for pag)
rm -f ~/bin/Linux-i686/mozilla
ln -fs /usr/local/mozilla/mozilla ~/bin/Linux-i686
(cd ~/bin/Linux-i686; ln -s mozilla netscape)
# Version 2 (for laptop)
cd /usr/local/bin; sudo rm -f mozilla; sudo ln -s /usr/local/mozilla1.6/mozilla .

Customizations: see file "~/wisdom/pc-setup" (see Netscape section)

